HEADWORD: Myelencephalon
<hw>My`e*len*ceph"a*lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from Gr. <grk>myelo`s</grk> marrow + E. <ets>encephalon</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The brain and spinal cord; the
cerebro-spinal axis. Sometimes abbreviated to
<altname>myelencephal</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
metencephalon.</def> <rj><au>Huxley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
